('64', 'Offense', 'Duke Fade and Follow', '["https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=M25CffvlBE6KQ06vD2AW","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=Ft3ipv7lDxt1ECsgH5Az","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=ZfQyAOQPdIrJmPo8n3AZ","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=S4cIr1AmF8nRUq9kXqmt","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=mXblHOPfyLmN84CDxauZ","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=irCze742ApRRLeHTkGb9","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=dFjwkswcqpso4w00ruRF","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=bFyEY3DxYDMvs5KSOXAp"]'::jsonb, 'A play you can use vs a zone with shorty top center and on the crease. | If the crease Slides when you’re attacking the Middle - feed the crease. | If the crease Slides when you’re attacking the Middle and the 2 slide is there - Skip it to the corners. | If the adjacent player slides - Draw and Dump on the wing. | The Duke Fade and Follow Offense attacks the middle using rollbacks - great spacing and a Weave.
