(NULL, 'Clearing', 'Skeleton Clears', '["https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=rGeK9SpsldV6jkFh328n","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=KcRfug6JkP4Wo3ABWd60","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=1mxUE8zB8gQ0ilmlTJcy","https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=dbBI7s9YNjCycslnCSmQ"]'::jsonb, 'The 2-2-3 Clear is just like a 4-3 clear except the midfielders cross the midline to bring riding players over the midline which should create more space and not let attackman and midfielders set traps and double too easily. | The 4 - 3 Clear puts 4 players across the midline and 3 players building the base of the clear. The upfield players will work back to the ball and turn upfield. | The Diamond Clear creates a diamond with the upfield defenseman on the off box side - both short stick midfielders in the middle (one restraining line - one midline) - and the LSM at the box. | The Shorty Low Clear or Punt Return is used when a team has an extremely athletic and elusive player that can easily run the ball out. He will wait inside to get the ball and then run it to the offensive side of the field.', '["<iframe width=\"500\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=rGeK9SpsldV6jkFh328n\" style=\"max-width: 100%\"></iframe>","<iframe width=\"500\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=KcRfug6JkP4Wo3ABWd60\" style=\"max-width: 100%\"></iframe>","<iframe width=\"500\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=1mxUE8zB8gQ0ilmlTJcy\" style=\"max-width: 100%\"></iframe>","<iframe width=\"500\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://lacrosse.labradorsports.com/play?l=dbBI7s9YNjCycslnCSmQ\" style=\"max-width: 100%\"></iframe>"]'::jsonb, NULL, NULL, NULL, FALSE, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://vimeo.com/', NULL, NULL, '2025-08-05T04:08:10.824Z', '2025-08-05T04:08:10.824Z');
